        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-12-11T15:55:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For these registers, the two structures are laid out identically, and you could just write a memcpy() from out-\u003eregs to context.X over 29 registers.\n\n(You used x86 as a template here, but the equivalent structures on x86 weren’t laid out identically, so we couldn’t write a simple memcpy().)",
      "revId": "5461373818b006ba49158b6c05328cf314195886",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
